    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-04-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-04-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="269"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d269">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01/4–449: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-04-04">April 4,
                            1949</date>.<lb/>[Received April 4—11:05 p. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>702. Official Kmt organ <hi rend="italic">Chung Tang Jih Pao</hi> April 4 quotes
                    Government spokesman re Executive Yuan status as follows: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“The Government spokesman said: ‘Since formation of new Cabinet, heads of
                            Ministries and commissions have gathered in Nanking, and this has led
                            some people to think that Government has returned to Nanking. Actually,
                            the seat of Government at present is still at Canton. Heads of
                            Ministries and commissions are only in Nanking temporarily to assist
                            Premier Ho Ying-chin in carrying out political functions. All routine
                            administrative functions are still performed at Canton. This policy was
                            decided by Sun Cabinet, and Premier Ho has not altered this
                            decision.’”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>It is learned, paper continues, that an “Executive Yuan Nanking office” is to be
                    established at OMEA<note n="86" xml:id="d269fn86">Officers Moral Endeavor
                        Association.</note> premises for handling affairs which must be settled in
                    Nanking.</p>
                <p>Sent Department 702, repeated OffEmb Canton and Shanghai unnumbered.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
